events.name: Build Actions On Google With Dialogflow | GDG Nagpur Launch
events.description:
Hello Developers,
The wait is finally over. Google Developer Group Nagpur is excited to share and invite you to our launch meetup, brings together developers from around the Nagpur for talks, hands-on learning with tech enthusiast, and the first look at Google’s latest developer products.

For your information, GDGs are local groups of developers who are specifically interested in Google products and APIs. Each local group is called a GDG chapter and can host a variety of technical activities for developers - from just a few people getting together to watch our latest videos to large gatherings with demos and tech talks, to hackathons.

By the motive of learning new skills, We came up with an exciting topic on the day which helps you build your own chatbot using Dialogflow.

Action on Google, can easily reach and engage with users across Google. From quick commands to full conversations, Actions help you connect your content and services to users with the Google Assistant. The conference will consist of cool and vibrant events and will concentrate on "Everyday Google" and will contain talks and discussions by developers on Google technologies used in everyday life like Google Assistant, Firebase, Tensrflow, etc.

Our Speaker Mr. Ashutosh Malve (AI/ML Enthusiast, Google Developer Group Nagpur ) will deliver the talk on:

1. Building great Actions for the Google Assistant.
2. Benefits and perks of Google Assistant Developer Community Program.

Note: Keep your laptop with you.

Thanks and Regards,
GDG Nagpur Team

#GDGNagpur #GDG #WTM

In case of any query feel free to contact us at [masked]

events.name: Machine Learning & TensorFlow Meetup

venue.name: G. H. Raisoni College of Engineering

events.description:
We’re super excited to bring together a diverse mix of machine learning enthusiast for technical talks, demos, and conversation with the TensorFlow Experts and community.

This meetup is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their everyday projects, and who wish to benefit from the power of TensorFlow wrapped in convenient higher-level abstractions. This is a great opportunity for professionals, entrepreneurs, and students to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

**Register yourself at http://bit.ly/mltf_meetup

Requirement:
**Bring Your Laptop!**

Agenda:
10:00 -Event Start & Opening Keynote
10:30 -Getting Started with Machine Learning
11:00 -Overview of TensorFlow
11:30 -Break
12:00 -Hands' on with TensorFlow
01:30 -Closing Keynote & Networking

Thanks and Regards,
GDG Nagpur Team

upcoming.name: Cloud Study Jam
upcoming.description:
Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud technologies as a team.
Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with Google Cloud Platform.

After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire
Qwiklabs catalog, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

**Register yourself at http://bit.ly/studyjamv1

Agenda:

Welcome!
- Opening Keynote
- Introduction to Virtual Machine
Lab 1: Creating a Virtual Machine
Lab 2: Getting Started with Cloud Shell and gcloud
- Break & Networking
Lab 3: Kubernetes Engine and Quick Start
Lab 4: Hosting your Website on App Engine
- Closing Keynote and Thank You

Note: Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Thanks and Regards,
GDG Nagpur Team
